< Review>
One of the few car wash locations in San Francisco. Fast and efficient! On a Saturday morning, I was in and out in about 25 mins, and that was with "The works" service. I also noticed that if you had kids with you, the friendly owner would offer toys or other distractions for the wait, which was a nice touch. Prices are reasonable for the area, so if you're like me and used to go to touchless car washes at gas stations, this is a much better upgrade. I'll definitely be back!<//Review>

For $50 "The Works" , you get an unfinished carwash inside and out. Quality has declined and I know I won't be returning.
You drive away with suds left on your side mirrors, dripping water from your license plates (front and back), and trunk. The interior was barely wiped clean. I could've gotten an exterior wash and did  the interior myself and that would have been more value for my money.  Based on my previous experience and the reviews, it's a hit and miss. I prefer to go to a place where I can count on good quality service.<//review>

< Review>
I wanted to invest in putting some quality bass for my 2015 BMW X5. I had a few ideas of what exactly I wanted, but needed more reference and information for my ride. I researched other car audio sites, but ONLINE CAR STEREO provided me with the intel to make my decision. They proved to be the right choice. I purchased a KICKER 46TL7T124 (12' self-enclosed subwoofer), along with a JL RD1000 (amplifier). Their knowledgeable staff assured me both items were more than compatible with one another. So much, that if I wanted to upgrade my system, it wouldn't be too much of a task. The sound generating from my components was very crisp and clear. Zero to no distortion and quality bass. I was very pleased with my purchase! I would definitely recommend shopping from ONLINE CAR STEREO to anyone who is looking to upgrade their car sounds...!!!< /Review>

< name>
Nathaniel Hambelton<//name>
<Time>1575950326546<//Time><rate>5</rate><Review>I've gone there maybe about five to six times now, and the service has always been excellent.  The hamburgers are all I really can give an opinion on, but for the price point I would say that they are very good. And are comparable to the products of places that sell their hamburgers for around 5 to $6 more. I go there with my family at least twice a month, and I have yet to have a bad experience. the only small gripe I have, is that when I order a rare hamburger it usually comes out medium to medium rare. But, I can fully understand that due to the risks of a lawsuit if someone does happen to get food poisoning. It is a good family diner, and does include a small arcade. If you take time to read this, I recommend at least trying the place out. My favorite is the "Heater" a mildly spicy burger with jalepeneos, sirrachia sauce, and pepperjack cheese as it's focus.< /Review><Pics>None<//Pics><Resp>None< /Resp>< GmapID>

This place is awful from beginning to end. It started with the check in. We booked through priceline, and it said that check in was at 4 am. Not the most unusual thing that I've experienced. I rang the bell at the front desk, and proceeded to wait 10 minutes for a person to answer. The man that did treated me like an idiot. Said that check-in wasn't until 2 pm. Okay, sure. We went found a place to catch some missed sleep. Came back at 2. Charged a hidden 100 fee, and the parking that was advertised as first-come was actually a pay-to-park, parking. <user>105490471369892114291< /user><rate>4</rate><Response>None< /Response><name>Tony Curatolo< /name></record>

<rating>4< /rating>< Text>
The Good.
Comfortable newer bed, Large newer TV, The excellent coffee machine, the price.
Also for me the location was good considering it is about a 15 min walk to the L.A. live entertainment area.

The Bad.
The parking (5 parking spots total and one of them are handicapped). The building is old like alot of other buildings in the area but the room I had was recently and decently remodeled considering what they have to work with.

Other thoughts..... This place needs more parking. I was afraid to move my car once I got there knowing the free parking spot would be gone when I got back.
Across the street is a Ramada Inn. They don't have the good coffee machine like The Staples Center Inn but their parking situation is better. I paid $25 more a night to stay there after two nights at SCI. In my opinion it was worth it mostly because of the parking plus the rooms are larger and had a hot tub. Still a bit run down like SCI but it had what I needed and then some.< /Text>

<rating>3<//rating></record></dataset><record>
<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
The bronze Mechanics Monument was created by sculptor Douglas Tilden and dedicated in 1901.

Tilden was born in Chico, California, in 1860. At age four, he contracted scarlet fever which left him deaf and mute for life.

Tilden attended the California School for the Deaf and UC Berkeley, then he studied art in Paris.

The Mechanics Monument was commissioned to honor industrialist Peter Donahue, founder of the San Francisco & North Pacific Railroad.

The bronze depicts five men struggling to punch a hole through a metal plate with a punch press. At the base are symbols of Donahue's professions: an anvil represents foundries, a propeller represents shipping, and the driving wheel and connecting rod represent railroads.

When the monument was dedicated, many citizens were shocked by the sight of rude mechanicals cavorting in the street without their knickers. Editorials demanded that Tilden put trousers on the men, an interesting aesthetic and technical challenge. Tilden ignored the controversy and it faded away.<//Review>
<response>None< /response>< username>
NoeHill Webmaster</username>

< Review>
I was looking to get a good upper body workout and got exactly that. The day I went, the winds were very strong and the waves were somewhat choppy. By the time I finished, my arms and back were beat.

The SUP shop trailer is fairly easy to spot from the street, so it isn‚Äôt too hard to find. Parking lots are available near the trailer and street parking was pretty easy as well, if you don‚Äôt mind the walk. Walk in‚Äôs are welcome but I strongly suggest making reservations online when going on holidays or weekends.

Everyone at the shop was very friendly and super helpful. Ryan and his coworker were kind enough to share some sunscreen with us, and they even have a nice shoe/sandal rack so that you don‚Äôt have to leave them on the beach. For the beginners in our group, they gave everyone a quick tutorial to get things going, and even helped bring the boards out into the water for those who had trouble.

Their equipment was overall well maintained and other than the loose rubber on my paddle board, I had no issues. The kayaks even looked like they had back rests! Rentals run about $30 an hour.

Love the views, great service and a fun activity to do while in the area. Had a wonderful experience at Mothers Beach, thanks Pro Sup Shop!< /Review>

< text>
Fiendly staff and excellent service!!
They rent single Kayaks (25$/hour), double kayaks (35$/hour) and stand up paddle boards (25$/hour). They are located at mother's beach (the location in google maps is pretty accurate). Although paddling is pretty easy and doesn't need much experience, if it's your first time they will give you an introduction on how to paddle before getting into the water.
If you wish to paddle in marina del ray area this place is highly recommended.<//text>

< review>
Had a great time at out on the bay this morning. I thought padding in the Marina with all the boats would make the experience crowded and a bit dangerous. However, I found it strangely comforting and connecting with the others engaging in water activities (kayaking, sailing, boat tours). For the most part the water was smooth with occasional turbulence calls cause by passing boats. Over all very pleasant experience. I will caution to pay attention the return trip, easy to confuse the right boat path.</review>

< review>
I only post reviews when extremely impressed or disappointed. Unfortunately, despite the great reviews that led me to choose Buy Any Tires Depot (BATD) and feeling good about 4 used tires for $300, I now describe how it played out over the past 4 months.

The Manager, Jesus, is a jovial guy who seems honest and helpful. But after 3 months, when my van began to shudder at 65mph+, I sought multiple opinions. Two other tire shop techs said the tires were out of balance, needed alignment, etc. and also said these tires were weather cracked and unsafe (though I suspected their opinion was biased). I spoke to Jesus (BATD) about it and he promptly spoke negatively about other tire shops as if his opinion is unbiased/reliable and others are not. He stated the tires did show some weather-wear but that most tires do in SoCal and that these were "good tires" with another year left on them. I asked him to re-balance the tires (so he did) but stated they were already balanced well. The shudder at 65mph+ continued.

Soon after, my father-in-law, a 40 year mechanic, was in town  and detected the preliminary stages of tread separation. He stated that this happens when used tires are mistakenly mounted in the opposite direction they were previously spinning. This can cause the tire to shred apart incurring immediate danger and damage to the vehicle. He suggested replacing the tires as soon as possible. Since my father-in-law has nothing at stake except my family's safety I value his opinion.

I then inquired with Jesus about new tires for my other vehicle to hear his views regarding used vs. new. He said he puts new tires on all his cars. I‚Äôd done extensive research on new tires so was unimpressed when he recommended poorly reviewed tires. I asked why he recommends low quality tires. He said he puts on new, cheap tires every two years and replaces them when they wear out. I'm not interested in this practice. So I bought 4 new tires; 2 at American Tire Depot and 2 at Redlands Tire Pros.  They gave me the same price, though RTP did not charge me for the rear alignment because they said it passed. (Kudos to them - they could've hidden that info and charged me anyway.) The shudder vanished.

So I returned to BATD. Jesus was less smiley than usual when he saw 4 new tires on my van. I pulled the 4 used tires out of my van and said I was returning them because the tread was separating. His response was that they were ‚Äúbad tires‚Äù from American Tire Depot. I said, "No, I bought these used from you when you said they were a good tire." His response was that this was American Tire Depot's in-house tire that was known to cause problems. I resolved to write this review. I'd purchased those tires after Jesus recommended them over a cheaper used tire he had in his shop. My $300 got me 4 months and a lot of verbal smoke and mirrors. I do NOT trust BATD and believe they will say and do anything to convince you they are  honest and giving you the best deal in town. They lost my business by refusing to offer any kind of refund on ‚Äúbad tires‚Äù they recommended and installed incorrectly. They also lost it by criticizing others rather than taking responsibility for their actions.

SIDENOTE: The same week I bought these 4 used tires from BATD, they rotated the tires on my Mazda 3 but within the first mile I noticed a tremendously loud humming. I drove back to BATD. Jesus said it was just a groove on the tires and that after 100-300 miles it'd smooth out. I left the next day, drove to San Jose and back the day after; 800 miles. The hum never dissipated. When arriving back home, I went to BATD to resolve the issue. Jesus said the rear shocks were bad, were causing ‚Äúcupping‚Äù on the tires and it all needed to be replaced. This turned out to be true and I wondered why he didn‚Äôt tell me this in the first place.

BOTTOM LINE: If a reviewer is initially happy due saving money, so was I. But time has revealed that BATD let me down on multiple levels in 2 different vehicle situations. Initially happy ‚Ä¶ eventually disappointed ‚Ä¶ and out $300 which BATD is shrugging off.< /review>

I told them well I should of been informed cause I could of took my self to another dentist. Because of the pain I was in my blood pressure was high. I told her thats what I‚Äôve been taken and it wasn‚Äôt working, she said because it‚Äôs open and it needs to be filled and left the room. <rating>1</rating>< Text>
This place deserves a negative star. We took all three kids there for their annual check up. The appointment was at 1 and an hour and a half later we still weren't seen. They stated our wait was due to insurance issues. My husband works for insurance so the insurance issues were actually due to laziness on their part. When I asked them again about how long the wait would be, the staff was rude.

Two out of the 3 children luckily didn't need anything other than a cleaning. My oldest child however, needed to have two extractions. There team of Dentists and Dental assistants had no communication between each other. It makes me wonder if they even pulled out the right teeth, especially after they were going to put on the sealant at the end and didn't know which teeth needed to be sealed. Their equipment was rusty and the time in between procedures was unacceptable. This job wasn't done by just one person, it was done by multiple people on the staff.

As we left, my other daughter said she heard one of the Dental Assistants yelling at another patient. Unprofessional and totally uncalled for. I feel so bad for my children. They should not have had to go through this experience to get their teeth cleaned. It is experiences like this that make people fear the dentist.

I would not recommend this place to anybody. In fact, we plan on reporting them. They are dirty, unprofessional, rude and don't take anybody's time into consideration.</Text>
